last_updated: 2026-04-28T14:32:00Z
last_updated_by: main
---

# Angel: src/auth (folder)

## Charter
Owns all authentication logic.


[CURRENT PHASE: REVIEW]
Read the brief below and evaluate the proposed change against your charter, invariants, and the current state of your folder.

You must respond with one of:
- "proceed": The change is safe. You have no concerns.
- "concerns": You have specific concerns. List them. Suggest mitigations in PROCEED IF.
- "refuse": The change fundamentally violates your invariants. Explain why, citing the violated invariant IDs (e.g. INV-002).

Do NOT modify any code or files during REVIEW. Only write the response file.

[YOUR FOLDER CONTENTS]
session.ts
middleware.ts
index.ts

[CHAT HISTORY]
(no chat history)

[NEWSPAPER DELTA SINCE YOUR LAST ACTIVATION]
(no new entries)

[YOUR INBOX]
--- URGENT CABLE ---
FROM: src-api
TO: src-auth
TIMESTAMP: 2026-04-28T14:30:00Z
TYPE: breaking_change
URGENCY: high
SUBJECT: Breaking change in session API
REQUIRES_ACK: true

BODY:
The session.create() signature changed from positional args to config object.
--- END CABLE ---

[BRIEF]
TO: src-auth
FROM: main
TIMESTAMP: 2026-04-28T15:00:00Z
PHASE: review
TYPE: change_request

TASK:
Add rate limiting to login endpoint

CONTEXT:
Users are brute-forcing passwords

EXPECTED SCOPE:
middleware.ts

PRIOR RESPONSE: none

[OUTPUT INSTRUCTIONS]
Write your response to: /project/.angels/_responses/src-auth/2026-04-28T1500-001.md
Write your response file at the path above. It MUST be a single JSON object — UTF-8, no markdown code fences, no commentary before or after the object. The parser is strict: an unknown field, a missing required field, or invalid JSON fails the whole invocation.

Fields (required: format_version, from, timestamp, verdict; all others optional and default to empty):
- "format_version": the literal number 1.
- "from": your angel ID (string).
- "timestamp": ISO-8601 timestamp (string).
- "verdict": exactly one of "proceed" | "concerns" | "refuse" | "done" | "error". Any other string fails the parser. Phase guide: review → proceed | concerns | refuse; discovery / init / execute / sweep / ask → done (or error on failure).
- "write_mode": "proposed" (default) unless your brief explicitly tells you to use "direct", "chunk" or "chunk_final".
- "concerns": string. Your concerns, or why you refuse.
- "proposed_plan": string. <the plan you propose for executing the brief>
- "questions_for_main": string. Questions for the main agent, if any.
- "proceed_if": string. Conditions under which concerns would be resolved.
- "test_results": string. Test results if you ran tests.
- "drift_report": string. Drift findings (sweep).
- "cables_sent": array of {"to": "<angel-id>", "type": "<cable type>"} objects.
- "files_changed": array of project-relative path strings.
- "angel_md_updated": boolean.

Rules:
- "cables_sent", "files_changed" and "angel_md_updated" are only valid when verdict is "done". On any other verdict they must be [] / [] / false (or omitted).
- verdict "concerns" requires a non-empty "proposed_plan".
- Multi-line text goes INSIDE the JSON strings (use \\n); do not add fields.

Minimal valid example:
{
  "format_version": 1,
  "from": "<your angel ID>",
  "timestamp": "<ISO-8601, e.g. 2026-05-12T14:32:00.000Z>",
  "verdict": "proceed",
  "proposed_plan": "..."
}

When sending cables to other angels, write .md files directly to .angels/_inbox/<receiver-angel-id>/. Do NOT use markdown headers (# ##). Use EXACTLY this format — deviations will break the receiver's inbox:

FROM: <your-angel-id>
TO: <receiver-angel-id>
TIMESTAMP: <ISO-8601>
TYPE: <one of: breaking_change | fyi | review_request | invariant_violation>
URGENCY: <one of: high | normal | low>
SUBJECT: <one-line summary - NEVER put body content here>
REQUIRES_ACK: <true | false>

BODY:
<multi-line body>

REFERENCES:
- <optional ref 1>
- <optional ref 2>
When done, exit. Do not loop or wait for input."
`;

